PARIS _ Both skiers and ski resort operators in the Alps live for snow, but some of the heaviest snowfalls this century turned deadly this winter, setting off a series of avalanches in February.
For all but the hardest-hit resort, in Galtuer, Austria, where 32 ski vacationers and 6 villagers died in a devastating slide Feb. 23, fear of more tragedies has gradually receded as warmer weather has packed down the snow.
